OL,3,CCutting NHS waiting times likely to
OL,4,Ctop Welsh spending plans in Budget
OL,6,FFailing to pass the budget will have
OL,7,Fserious consequences. If there's no
OL,8,Fmajority by the end of the process,
OL,9,F75% of current spending plans continue
OL,10,Finto the new year.
OL,12,FIt could affect the amount available
OL,13,Ftoo, preventing the extra money
OL,14,Fearmarked for Wales by the UK
OL,15,FGovernment from being spent and
OL,16,Freducing the tax yield in Wales by up
OL,17,Fto #3bn - a potential windfall for
OL,18,FWelsh taxpayers but a big cut for
OL,19,Fpublic services.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G13/15
